en to your office inbox, what Alaska has given to your liquor cabinet, and how a speech given by a bumbling North Carolinian gave us a word for impenetrable nonsense. Surprising, entertaining, and illuminating, this is essential reading for armchair travelers and word nerds. Our dictionaries are full of hidden histories, tales, and adventures from all over the world—if you know where to look.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEnglish languagexEtymology. 0aNames, Geographical. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  alanguage, linguistics, place, geography, popular culture, aphorisms, cliche, etymology, panama hats, brazil nuts, limericks, great dane, siamese twins, xanadu, daiquiri cocktail, cayenne pepper, jalapeno, klondike, geyser, bikini, antimacassar, manila, bedlem, mocha, timbuktu, conga, canary, tangerine, magenta, spa, vaudeville, nonfiction, word origins, phrases, sayings.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226682822423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226682822/original  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles